-- =====================================================================
-- Round 72 — backfill 621 sales_transactions rows from the master
-- Dialysis Comp Work MASTER.xlsx that were missing from our DB.
--
-- BACKGROUND
-- ----------
-- R70 documented a ~80bps cap-rate gap between our charts and the
-- master Excel (master 8.6-9.2% vs ours 7.7-8.1% in 2009). R72
-- traces the root cause: master has ~1,040 sales we don't, and 621
-- of those have an existing property_id in our DB so they can be
-- inserted directly. The remaining 419 have no matching property and
-- would require property records to be created first (separate batch).
--
-- IMPACT (projected)
-- ------------------
-- 621 new sales_transactions rows tagged data_source='master_xlsx_backfill_r72'.
-- Year distribution: pre-2014 ~76 rows (closes early 80bps gap),
-- 2014-2025 ~545 rows (general enrichment).
--
-- All rows include cap_rate / stated_cap_rate / initial_cap_rate when
-- the master had them. property_id is set; tenant goes into notes for
-- audit.
--
-- ROLLBACK
-- --------
--   DELETE FROM sales_transactions WHERE data_source = 'master_xlsx_backfill_r72';
--
-- IDEMPOTENCY
-- -----------
-- INSERT uses ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING against (property_id, sale_date,
-- sold_price) — if a sale already exists at that (property_id, date,
-- price) we skip. There's no unique constraint on that tuple by
-- default, so we use a manual EXISTS guard via WHERE NOT EXISTS in a
-- CTE wrapper. Safe to re-run.
--
-- HOW THIS WAS GENERATED
-- ----------------------
-- 1. Extracted master's 2,551 Sales Comps rows (date+cap+price+addr).
-- 2. Matched each against our sales_transactions on (date, addr) and
--    (date ± 90d, price). 1,510 master rows matched ours; 1,041 did
--    not — those are "master has, we don't".
-- 3. For each master-unmatched row, looked up an existing property_id
--    via (state, address-first-number, normalized-street) exact match
--    plus a 2-word-prefix fuzzy fallback. 621 found a property.
-- 4. Emitted one INSERT row per match.
--
-- The script lives in /tmp/backfill_plan.json on the workstation that
-- ran R72 audit; see audit/cm-style-audit/R72-USER-NOTES-2026-05-24.md
-- for the full process narrative.
-- =====================================================================

